<title>See Also</title>

<section><title>Related Resources</title>
<para>
Apart from using Eiffel compilers, there is no real equivalent of 
<projectname>gelint</projectname>.
</para>

<para>
<ulink url="http://www.eiffel.com">ISE</ulink>'s 
<ulink url="https://www.eiffel.org/doc/eiffelstudio/Eiffel%20Inspector">Eiffel Inspector</ulink>
goes beyond the scope of <projectname>gelint</projectname> and
detects suspicious code usages in otherwise valid Eiffel code.
</para>

<para>
The definitions of the Eiffel validity rules reported by
<projectname>gelint</projectname> can be found in the
<ulink url="http://www.ecma-international.org/publications/standards/Ecma-367.htm">ECMA Eiffel standard</ulink>.
It is also available as an 
<ulink url="https://www.iso.org/standard/42924.html">ISO standard</ulink>.
</para>
</section>
